# ðŸŽ² Dice Roller Game (Python)

A simple and beginner-friendly Python command-line game that simulates rolling a dice!

---

## ðŸ“Œ Game Overview

This is a fun terminal game where the user rolls a virtual dice. Every time you press Enter, a new random number between 1 and 6 is shown.

---

## ðŸ§  How the Code Works (Line-by-Line Table)

| Line | Code | Explanation |
|------|------|-------------|
| 1 | `import random` | Import the random module to generate random numbers. |
| 3-4 | `def roll_dice(): return random.randint(1, 6)` | Define a function to roll the dice which returns a random number between 1 and 6. |
| 6 | `print("...")` | Display welcome message. |
| 7 | `while True:` | Start an infinite loop so the player can keep rolling. |
| 8 | `input(...)` | Wait for the user to press Enter to roll the dice. |
| 9 | `number = roll_dice()` | Call the dice rolling function. |
| 10 | `print(...)` | Show the result of the roll. |
| 12 | `input(...)` | Ask if the user wants to roll again. |
| 13-15 | `if...break` | If the user types anything other than "yes", the game stops. |

